Roy Hodgson has been confirmed as the new Crystal Palace manager for upcoming Premier League season after the club announced he would be staying at the helm. The 75-year-old guided Palace to English top-flight safety after being brought in to replace Patrick Vieira midway through last season and will stay in his position as head coach for the new campaign. Confirming the news on social media, Palace tweeted: ‘We’re pleased to announce that Roy Hodgson has been appointed Crystal Palace manager for the 23/24 season ‘He will lead the side into next season alongside Paddy McCarthy as assistant manager, Ray Lewington as coach and Dean Kiely as goalkeeper coach.’ More to follow.